details.description: Borboleta Café is a vibrant, community-focused coffee shop located in the heart of Rock Hill, SC. Our mission is to create a welcoming, safe space where coffee lovers can connect, grow, and be inspired. We proudly serve high-quality, locally roasted coffee from Pure Intentions and offer a menu full of carefully crafted espresso drinks, teas, fresh pastries, and more. Whether you're looking to fuel your day with a delicious cup of coffee, attend one of our financial literacy workshops, or simply enjoy a cozy corner to relax- Borboleta Café is here to nourish your body and mind.

reviews_data.review_text: I really like their matcha, their flavored cold foams are delicious, and the shape of the cups is very aesthetically pleasing 😂 I took one star off because I do not like that they don't display prices on the menu. I almost fell over when I saw my total. I think price transparency is important especially in this economy.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Nicole,
Thank you so much for your thoughtful review! We’re so glad you enjoyed the matcha, our cold foams, and the look of our cups — we love bringing a little extra joy to each drink. 😊
We appreciate you sharing your thoughts on pricing transparency — it’s a valid point, and something we’re working to improve in-store. In the meantime, our full menu with pricing is available online for anyone who’d like to browse ahead of time.

Thanks again for visiting — we look forward to welcoming you back soon! 🦋

reviews_data.review_text: Cute decor, super clean, nice atmosphere. The tea was pretty good! Not the best I’ve had but I would buy again for the price. ☕️ Staff were friendly but it was ridiculously slow. Came in mid day on a Sunday and it took over 20 minutes for 1 herbal tea! If they were packed and busy that would be understandable but the girl at the counter was literally just standing and talking with 3 male customers non stop. I would not return if this is the regular time frame.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Mary Rose!

Thank you so much for visiting and for taking the time to share your feedback. We’re so glad you enjoyed the decor, atmosphere, and cleanliness!

We do recall your visit! We’re sorry to hear about the wait you experienced. We believe your visit may have been on Saturday which was one of our busiest days. The individuals you saw at the counter were also placing their orders at the time, and while we do our best to move efficiently, we steep each tea fresh to order — which can occasionally add to the wait.
That said, your feedback is truly helpful. We’re working to improve how we set clear expectations for wait times and will continue training our team to better manage flow even during busy stretches.

We’d really love the chance to welcome you back for a smoother experience and to share more of our delicious tea offerings with you!

Warmly,
Genessis
Owner, Borboleta Cafe 🦋

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Mary Rose!

Thank you so much for visiting and for taking the time to share your feedback. We’re so glad you enjoyed the decor, atmosphere, and cleanliness!

We do recall your visit! We’re sorry to hear about the wait you experienced. We believe your visit may have been on Saturday which was one of our busiest days. The individuals you saw at the counter were also placing their orders at the time, and while we do our best to move efficiently, we steep each tea fresh to order — which can occasionally add to the wait.
That said, your feedback is truly helpful. We’re working to improve how we set clear expectations for wait times and will continue training our team to better manage flow even during busy stretches.

We’d really love the chance to welcome you back for a smoother experience and to share more of our delicious tea offerings with you!

Warmly,
Genessis
Owner, Borboleta Cafe 🦋

reviews_data.review_text:
Forget the other coffee places in Rock Hill... dont even think about trying to find a better place in Charlotte. This is the spot!

Coffee is amazing! The temperature is fantastic, and the flavor is amazing.

This is the ambrosia of the gods!

Oh, and flavor wise, the coffee isn't sour and tastes like actual coffee, not burnt like Dunkin or Starbucks! It's local and independently owned.

Oh, and atmosphere! Calm music, great little tables, and chairs i could spend hours here just working.

Don't even worry about parking. You have a whole parking lot to choose from.

Now there are cons... I want more couches to lounge in while I read... I know picky picky me, but hey, I can always ask.

Love this place! (^_^)/"
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much for your incredible review! We’re beyond grateful for your support and love hearing that our coffee and atmosphere hit the mark for you.

And guess what? We heard you! Because of your feedback, there’s now a cozy couch waiting for you to lounge in while you read. We always appreciate input from our amazing guests, and we’re so happy to make our space even better for you. Looking forward to seeing you again soon! 🦋
